KS_MayaSmartRename - Maya Bulk Rename Tool
==============================================

What is this?
-------------
KS_MayaSmartRename is a Maya utility for bulk renaming scene objects using a
safe, preview-first workflow. It is designed to work with joints, transforms,
controls, locators, meshes, and most named Maya nodes.

The tool was created as the Maya counterpart to KS_SmartRename for Unity, but
focused around common rigging and animation-pipeline naming workflows inside
Maya.

KS_MayaSmartRename currently supports three rename modes:

- Sequential Rename
- Search / Replace
- Prefix / Suffix Only

The tool provides a live preview before any changes are applied, allows items
to be manually reordered, validates generated names before renaming, and wraps
the rename operation in a single Maya undo chunk.


What does it do?
----------------

KS_MayaSmartRename performs the following operations:

- Loads the current Maya selection into a rename table
- Adds additional selected objects without clearing the current list
- Supports manual rename ordering with Move Up, Move Down, and Reverse
- Builds a live preview showing Current Name -> Preview Name
- Allows individual rows to be enabled or disabled before applying
- Applies sequential numbering based on the visible tool order
- Supports Search / Replace with plain text, regex, case-sensitive, and
  whole-word options
- Supports adding a prefix and/or suffix while preserving the current name
- Detects invalid Maya names before applying
- Detects duplicate names within the batch
- Warns when a generated name already exists in the scene
- Copies valid preview names to the clipboard
- Selects highlighted table rows back in Maya
- Saves and loads rename settings from the Maya user preferences folder
- Applies renames inside one Maya undo chunk


How do I use it?
----------------

Setup
-----

1. Place KS_MayaSmartRename.py in your Maya scripts folder.

   Example:

      C:/Users/<username>/Documents/maya/2026/scripts/

2. Open Maya and run the tool from the Script Editor:

      import importlib
      import KS_MayaSmartRename
      importlib.reload(KS_MayaSmartRename)
      KS_MayaSmartRename.show()

   The reload version is recommended while actively editing the script.


Selection
---------

The Selection section is where you control which Maya objects are included in
the rename operation and in what order.

Buttons:

   Load Current Selection
      Clears the tool list and loads the current Maya selection.

   Add Selected
      Adds the current Maya selection to the existing list. Objects already in
      the list are skipped.

   Remove
      Removes the highlighted rows from the tool list. This does not delete
      anything from the Maya scene.

   Clear
      Clears all rows from the tool list. This does not affect the scene.

   Select Rows in Maya
      Selects the highlighted table rows in Maya. If no rows are highlighted,
      all enabled rows are selected instead.

   Move Up
      Moves the selected row up in the rename order.

   Move Down
      Moves the selected row down in the rename order.

   Reverse
      Reverses the full list order. This is useful for joint chains selected
      from tip to root instead of root to tip.

The rename order matters most in Sequential Rename mode because the numbering
is assigned based on the enabled item order in the tool list.


Preview Table
-------------

The preview table shows the current rename state for every loaded item.

Columns:

   Use
      Checked rows are included when Apply Rename is pressed. Unchecked rows
      are left unchanged.

   Type
      The Maya node type, such as joint, transform, mesh, locator, etc.

   Current Name
      The current short name of the Maya object.

   Preview Name
      The name that will be applied if the row is enabled and valid.

   Status
      Shows whether the row will be renamed or if there is an issue.

Common status messages:

   Will rename
      The row is enabled, the preview name is different, and no error was found.

   Invalid Maya characters
      The preview name contains characters that are not allowed by the tool's
      Maya-safe naming validation.

   Cannot start with number
      Maya node names should not start with a number. Add a prefix or use a
      different number placement.

   Duplicate in batch
      Two or more enabled rows are trying to use the same new name.

   Name exists in scene
      A node with the generated name already exists in the scene.


Rename Modes
------------

Sequential Rename
-----------------

Sequential Rename creates a new name for every enabled row using a base name,
optional prefix, optional suffix, and optional numbering.

This is the main mode for joint chains and rigging workflows.

Default convention:

      Spine_01_JNT
      Spine_02_JNT
      Spine_03_JNT

Fields:

   Prefix
      Text added before the generated name.

      Example:
         Prefix L_
         Result L_Spine_01_JNT

   Base Name
      The main name used for every enabled object.

      Example:
         Base Name Spine
         Result Spine_01_JNT, Spine_02_JNT, Spine_03_JNT

      Spaces and unsafe characters are cleaned into Maya-safe underscores.

   Suffix
      Text added after the generated name.

      Common examples:
         _JNT
         _CTRL
         _GEO
         _LOC
         _DRV

   Enable Numbering
      Turns sequential numbering on or off.

      On:
         Spine_01_JNT, Spine_02_JNT, Spine_03_JNT

      Off:
         Every enabled item previews the same base name, which will usually
         create duplicate warnings unless the name is unique.

   Start
      The number assigned to the first enabled item.

      Example:
         Start 1 -> Spine_01_JNT
         Start 5 -> Spine_05_JNT

   Step
      How much the number increases per item.

      Example:
         Start 1, Step 1 -> 01, 02, 03
         Start 1, Step 5 -> 01, 06, 11

   Padding
      Minimum number of digits in the number.

      Padding 2:
         01, 02, 10

      Padding 3:
         001, 002, 010

   Separator
      Text inserted between the base name and the number. Underscore is
      recommended.

      Example:
         Base Spine + Separator _ + Number 01 + Suffix _JNT
         Result Spine_01_JNT

   Number Position
      Controls where the number is placed.

      After Base:
         Spine_01_JNT

      At End:
         Spine_JNT_01

      Before Base:
         01_Spine_JNT
         L_01_Spine_JNT if a prefix is used

      Note:
         Names that start with a number are invalid and will be flagged in
         the preview.


Search / Replace
----------------

Search / Replace finds text in each current object name and replaces it.

Fields:

   Search For
      Text to find in each current name.

   Replace With
      Text that replaces the match. Leave blank to remove the matched text.

Options:

   Case Sensitive
      When enabled, the search must match capitalization exactly.

      Example:
         Searching for arm will not match Arm if Case Sensitive is enabled.

   Regex
      Treats Search For as a regular expression.

      Useful patterns:

         ^L_      matches L_ only at the start
         _JNT$    matches _JNT only at the end
         \\d+      matches one or more digits

      Invalid regex patterns are caught and shown in the preview status.

   Whole Word
      Only replaces the search text when it appears as a separate word-like
      token.

      Example with search term Arm:

         L_Arm_JNT      matches
         L_ForeArm_JNT  does not match

The preview updates live as you type.


Prefix / Suffix Only
--------------------

Prefix / Suffix Only keeps the current object name and adds text before and/or
after it.

This mode does not use a base name or numbering, so those controls are hidden
when this mode is active.

Example:

   Current:
      Spine_01_JNT

   Prefix:
      FK_

   Suffix:
      _DRV

   Result:
      FK_Spine_01_JNT_DRV


Preview Actions
---------------

The Rename Settings section includes utility buttons for controlling the
preview list.

   Select All
      Enables all rows in the table.

   Deselect All
      Disables all rows in the table.

   Changes Only
      Enables only rows where the preview name is different from the current
      name and has no error.

   Copy Preview Names
      Copies all enabled, valid preview names to the clipboard, one per line.

   Refresh Preview
      Rebuilds the preview table manually. Most fields already update live,
      but this is useful after scene changes.


Settings
--------

The tool can save and load its current rename settings.

   Save Settings
      Saves the current mode, prefix, suffix, numbering options, and
      search/replace options to the Maya user preferences folder.

   Load Settings
      Loads the previously saved settings.

The settings file is stored in the Maya user preferences directory as:

      KS_MayaSmartRename_prefs.json

The loaded settings do not store or restore the selected Maya objects. They
only store the rename options.


Applying
--------

1. Load or add objects to the Selection table.

2. Choose the rename mode.

3. Adjust the rename settings.

4. Review the Preview Name and Status columns.

5. Disable any rows you do not want to rename.

6. Click Apply Rename.

7. Confirm the rename dialog.

The rename operation is wrapped in one Maya undo chunk, so one Maya Undo should
revert the full rename pass.


Safety
------

KS_MayaSmartRename is preview-first. No scene changes are made until Apply
Rename is pressed.

Before applying, the tool checks for:

- Empty generated names
- Names that start with a number
- Invalid Maya characters
- Duplicate names inside the current batch
- Names that already exist in the scene

Rows with errors are blocked from applying until fixed or disabled.


Notes
-----

- The tool works on Maya scene nodes, not files on disk.
- It is intended for clean Maya short names, not namespace editing.
- The preview table uses short object names, but internally stores full DAG
  paths where available.
- Deepest objects are renamed first to reduce full-path invalidation issues
  when renaming hierarchy items.
- Prefix / Suffix Only mode uses the current object name as the base.
- Sequential Rename mode assigns numbers only to enabled rows.
- Search / Replace mode operates on the current name of each item.
- All renames are applied using maya.cmds.rename.
- The operation is undoable through Maya because it is wrapped in one undo chunk.
- Hover over any control in the tool to see a tooltip explaining what it does.


Limitations
-----------

- The tool currently validates names using a strict Maya-safe naming rule:
  names must start with a letter or underscore and contain only letters,
  numbers, and underscores.
- Namespace workflows are not currently supported.
- Attribute renaming is not supported.
- File, asset, and texture renaming outside the Maya scene is not supported.
- Shape-renaming behavior depends on Maya's default rename behavior and the
  selected node type.
- The settings file stores rename options only, not the current object list.
- Batch name collision detection is conservative and focused on preventing
  accidental conflicts.


Changelog
---------

v0.2.3
  - Added clear tooltips across the UI
  - Added detailed tooltip explanations for rename modes, numbering, regex,
    whole-word matching, preview status, and apply behavior
  - Added row-level preview table tooltips

v0.2.2
  - Hid Base Name row in Prefix / Suffix Only mode
  - Hid numbering controls in Prefix / Suffix Only mode to avoid confusion

v0.2.1
  - Fixed Prefix / Suffix Only mode interaction issue caused by reusing widgets
    across multiple layouts
  - Prefix and suffix fields now remain editable in Prefix / Suffix Only mode

v0.2.0
  - Added Search / Replace mode
  - Added Prefix / Suffix Only mode
  - Added Save Settings and Load Settings
  - Added Copy Preview Names
  - Added Select Rows in Maya
  - Shared validation and duplicate detection across all modes

v0.1.2
  - Added safer Maya short-name validation
  - Prevented preview crashes from invalid characters or names starting with
    numbers
  - Widened Start, Step, Padding, and Separator fields

v0.1.1
  - Updated defaults to match common rigging convention:
    Spine_01_JNT

v0.1.0
  - Initial release
  - Sequential Rename mode
  - Selection table
  - Manual ordering
  - Live preview
  - Apply Rename in one Maya undo chunk


